http://www.thehindu.com/sport/cricket/BCCI-to-invite-former-captains-for-500th-Test/article14410824.ece

 The BCCI has decided to invite all the former India captains to celebrate the occasion of the country’s 500th Test match that will be played against New Zealand in Kanpur from September 22.A specially minted silver coin with ‘500th Test’ embossed on it is being prepared for the toss.Senior BCCI official and UPCA supremo Rajeev Shukla said a host of events are being organised by the BCCI to make the event memorable.“The BCCI wants to felicitate all former captains during the Test match. Green Park is one of the first four Test venues in India along with Chepauk, Wankhede and Eden Gardens. “It will be a fitting tribute to all those former captains present on the occasion,” Shukla said on Thursday.The likes of Nari Contractor, Chandu Borde, Dilip Vengsarkar, Kapil Dev, Ravi Shastri, Sunil Gavaskar, Sourav Ganguly, Sachin Tendulkar, Virender Sehwag, and Krishnamachari Srikkanth are expected to grace the occasion.Chief coach Anil Kumble will also be present. Rahul Dravid is also expected to come back from his India A tour assignment.However, the BCCI may not invite Mohammad Azharuddin, who was banned for life for his alleged involvement in the match-fixing scandal. While Azhar has been acquitted by the court, the BCCI still does not invite him to official events. — PTI 